ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I could share my feelings with my parent.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: I felt that I could trust my parent as someone to talk to.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: If I told my parent about a problem, they would probably blame me for it.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: If something good happened to me, I could tell my parent about it.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: When I felt bad about something, my parent would listen.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: If I talked to my parent, I think they would try to understand how I felt.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: When I talked to my parent, they made me feel better.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: If I talked to my parent, they would have suggestions about how to handle problems.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: If I needed to know something about the world (like how things worked), I could ask my parent about it.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: When I had a problem with money, I could talk to my parent about it.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: If I needed help with my schoolwork, I could ask my parent about it.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: If I needed help getting somewhere, I could ask my parent for a way to get there.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: If I had a problem with my health, I thought I could talk to my parent about it.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: If I felt bored, my parents had suggestions about things to do.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: If I had a problem with a friend, my parent would have advice about what to do.
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderately so; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: Parental Support Inventory (PSI) score- Sum of all emotional support and instrumental support items' raw scores
Notes: Sum of psi_1_e to psi_7_e and psi_8_i to psi_15_i
